results.name: a(1)=5; for n >= 2, if n = Product p_i^e_i, then a(n) = Product p_{i+3}^e_i.
reference: From a puzzle proposed by _Marc LeBrun_.
example: If n = 9 = 3^2, then a(n) = 11^2 = 121 (since 11 is the thiord prime after 3).
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_
